<!-- SECTION 7: 7-STEP PROCESS -->
<section class="steps-section" id="procedure-section">
    <div class="section-container">
        <header class="section-header" style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:48px;">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Our Process</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">8 Steps to Convert Pvt Ltd to Public Ltd in Delhi</h2>
            <p class="section-subtitle" style="text-align:left;max-width:100%;">Patron's Pvt-to-Public conversion pipeline runs from pre-conversion eligibility review through shareholder base expansion to 7 minimum and director count to 3 minimum (1 Indian resident under Section 149(3)), board resolution to convene the EGM, EGM with 21 clear days notice and special resolution at 75 percent majority, Form MGT-14 filing within 30 days under Section 117, Form INC-27 filing within 15 days under Rule 33, ROC issuance of fresh Certificate of Incorporation and post-conversion governance setup including independent directors and committees where Section 149(4) / 177 / 178 thresholds will be crossed. Each step is a fixed deliverable - no surprises mid-engagement.</p>
        </header>
        <div class="steps-container">
            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-content">
                    <span class="step-badge">Step 1</span>
                    <h3 class="step-title">Pre-Conversion Eligibility Review</h3>
                    <p>Verify current shareholder count and director count; plan shareholder base expansion to minimum 7 and director count to minimum 3 (with 1 Indian resident); identify third director candidate; assess post-conversion governance thresholds for independent director, audit committee and NRC.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="step-visual">
                    <div class="step-illustration">
