<!-- SECTION 15A: LEGAL FRAMEWORK -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Legal and Compliance Framework</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>Primary Statute:</strong> Companies Act 2013.</p>
                <p><strong>Charging Section:</strong> Section 14 - Alteration of articles; the proviso requiring Central Government / Regional Director approval applies ONLY to the reverse direction (Public to Private), NOT to the upgrade direction.</p>
                <p><strong>Related Sections:</strong> Section 13 (alteration of Memorandum); Section 18 (conversion of companies already registered); Section 117 (filing of resolutions); Section 2(71) (Public Company definition); Section 3 (minimum 7 members); Section 149 (minimum 3 directors; 1 Indian resident under 149(3)).</p>
                <p><strong>Procedural Rules:</strong> Rule 33 of Companies (Incorporation) Rules 2014 - specifically governs Form INC-27 filing for Pvt to Public conversion.</p>
                <p><strong>Special Resolution Threshold:</strong> Section 114(2) - 75% of members present and voting at the EGM; requires 21 clear days of EGM notice under Section 101.</p>
                <p><strong>MGT-14 Filing:</strong> Section 117 - within 30 days of passing the special resolution; attachments include the special resolution, amended MOA, amended AOA, EGM notice and minutes.</p>
                <p><strong>INC-27 Filing:</strong> Rule 33 Companies (Incorporation) Rules 2014 - within 15 days of passing the special resolution; supporting documents include special resolution copy, amended MOA, amended AOA, EGM minutes.</p>
                <p><strong>Director Appointment (if needed):</strong> DIR-3 (DIN); DIR-2 (director consent); DIR-12 (notice of appointment); to be completed before EGM where new director count needs to reach 3.</p>
                <p><strong>Shareholder Expansion (if needed):</strong> Section 62 (further issue of share capital); PAS-3 (return of allotment); valuation under Section 247 where applicable.</p>
                <p><strong>Post-Conversion - Independent Directors:</strong> Section 149(4) + Rule 4 of Companies (Appointment and Qualification of Directors) Rules 2014 - applicable to listed Public Companies and unlisted Public Companies with paid-up share capital INR 10 crore or more, turnover INR 100 crore or more or aggregate outstanding loans / debentures / deposits INR 50 crore or more.</p>
                <p><strong>Post-Conversion - Audit Committee:</strong> Section 177 + Rule 6 of Companies (Meetings of Board and its Powers) Rules 2014 - same thresholds; chaired by an independent director; minimum 3 directors with majority independent.</p>
                <p><strong>Post-Conversion - NRC:</strong> Section 178 - same thresholds; minimum 3 non-executive directors with majority independent; chaired by an independent director.</p>
                <p><strong>Listed Public Companies - Additional:</strong> SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations 2015 - quarterly results in 45 days; annual results in 60 days; shareholding pattern quarterly; corporate governance report; related party disclosure; material event disclosure under Regulation 30.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority:</strong> Registrar of Companies (ROC), NCT of Delhi and Haryana, CGO Complex, Lodhi Road, New Delhi 110003. NO Regional Director involvement.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority for source verification:</strong> MCA21 v3 at <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mca.gov.in</a>, SEBI at <a href="https://www.sebi.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sebi.gov.in</a> and India Code (statutes) at <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">indiacode.nic.in</a>.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

